    • Method Detail

      • startGroup

        public void startGroup()
                throws IllegalStateException
        This method starts a new button-group and adds it to this container. All buttons (or widgets) added to this container until the button-group was ended will be added to the current button-group. A button-group is realized by UiWidgetButtonGroup. this toolbar.
        Specified by:
        startGroup in interface ButtonContainer
        Specified by:
        startGroup in interface UiWidgetAbstractButtonContainer
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if the previous button-group has NOT been ended.
        See Also:
        #addChild(UiWidgetRegular)

      • endGroup

        public boolean endGroup()
        This method ends a previously started group.
        Specified by:
        endGroup in interface ButtonContainer
        Returns:
        true if the current button-group has successfully been ended, false otherwise (if there was no such button-group).

      • addChild

        public void addChild(UiWidgetRegular child)
        This method adds the given child to the end of the child-list. For vertical layouts this will be the bottom and for horizontal layouts this will be the right.
